==Content agreement with Retirement Living TV==
On April 16, 2007, [[S-VOX]] signed an exclusive distribution agreement with [[Retirement Living TV]].  Under the terms of the deal, content from RLTV will air on One and [[VisionTV]].  In addition, the two broadcasters will co-produce original programming to be aired on S-VOX networks. [http://www.visiontv.com/Media/Releases/svox_rltv.html]

==History==
Licensed as ''Wisdom: Canada's Body, Mind & Spirit Channel'' by the [[Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission]] (CRTC) on [[November 24]], [[2000]]; the channel was launched as ''One: the Body, Mind & Spirit channel'' on [[September 7]], [[2001]].

On [[January 18]], [[2008]], a joint venture between [[Canwest]] and GS Capital Partners bought [[Alliance Atlantis]] and gained AAC's minority interest in One.

